Program: Omnibus
Title: Sir Thomas Sopwith
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jky
Last Broadcast Date: 15 February 1989
A look at the life and work of the pioneering aircraft builder Sir Thomas Sopwith whose career spans from Sopwith Camels and Pups used in WWI to Harrier vertical take-off jets used in the Falklands Conflict.